<reggrp_short_dscr>:
Table UPdata Engine (TUPE)
------------------------------
<reggrp_public_text>:
Engine - called "TUPE" - for updating VLAN_PORT_MASK in VLAN Table.

TUPE is used as follows:
1) Configure TUPE parameters.
2) Set TUPE_MISC.TUPE_START=1
3) Await TUPE_MISC.TUPE_START=0

While TUPE is running (i.e. TUPE_START=1) CPU must not write to VLAN table.

The VLAN table's TUPE_CTRL field as well as unused bits in VLAN_PORT_MASK can be used to control which VLAN table entries TUPE shall update. 

TUPE_CMD_PORT_MASK_CLR and TUPE_CMD_PORT_MASK_SET are used to specify the required changes to VLAN_PORT_MASK for those VLAN table enties, which shall be updated.
