<reggrp_public_text>:
The ARP Pointer Remap Table can be used to achieve faster failover if the next hop changes for a large number of LPM VCAP entries. 

To utilize the ARP Pointer Remap Table, the LPM VCAP action must be configured with ARP_PTR_REMAP_ENA=1. In that case the ARP_PTR in the VCAP action is used as a pointer into the ARP Pointer Remap Table. Lookup in this table then provides the ARP_PTR for lookup in the ARP Table (ANA_L3:ARP).
