Set if an IP MC frame copy from VD0 does not get L3 forwarded (i.e. gets dropped).

This may happen during normal operation if EVMID_MASK_MODE=0 is used and the ingress router leg is not located within the first EVMID_MASK in a linked list of EVMID_MASKs.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if neither L2 nor L3 forwarding is performed for an IP multicast frame.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set when IP multicast L3 forwarding has been completed for a frame.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an IP MC frame has failed RPF check.

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:L3MC:L3MC_CTRL.RPF_CHK_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set when L2 forwarding of IPv4 multicast frame has completed.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if a frame has been redirected to CPU due to ICMP Redirect check. 

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:VMID:RLEG_CTRL.RLEG_IP4_ICMP_REDIR_ENA
ANA_L3:VMID:RLEG_CTRL.RLEG_IP6_ICMP_REDIR_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if a frame has been redirected to CPU due to a zero DMAC address in the ARP entry.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set in case of an IP unicast frame being filtered due to TTL.
I.e. a frame with TTL<2 which hits a valid ARP table entry with non-zero MAC address.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if IP unicast routing lookup results in a valid ARP entry allowing the frame to be routed.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if ingress router leg match has been found for an IP multicast frame with a TTL less than 2.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set for successful IPv4 SIP security lookup, i.e. matching for (DMAC,SIP) and/or (VMID,SIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:SIP_SECURE_ENA.SIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set for successful IPv6 DIP security lookup, i.e. matching for (DMAC,DIP) and/or (VMID,DIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:DIP_SECURE_ENA.DIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set for successful IPv4 DIP security lookup, i.e. matching for (DMAC,DIP) and/or (VMID,DIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:DIP_SECURE_ENA.DIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set for successful IPv6 SIP security lookup, i.e. matching for (DMAC,SIP) and/or (VMID,SIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:SIP_SECURE_ENA.SIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if security lookup fails for DIP, i.e. mismatch for (DMAC,DIP) / (VMID,DIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:DIP_SECURE_ENA.DIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if security lookup fails for SIP, i.e. mismatch for (DMAC,DIP) / (VMID,DIP).

Related parameters:
ANA_L3:COMMON:SIP_SECURE_ENA.SIP_CMP_ENA
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an ingress router leg match has been found for an IP multicast frame.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an ingress router leg match has been found for an IP unicast frame.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if ingress router leg match has been found for an IPv4/IPv6 multicast frame with options/hop-by-hop options. 

Such frames may optionally be redirected to CPU, ref.
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_IP4_OPTIONS_REDIR_ENA
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_IP6_HOPBYHOP_REDIR_ENA

A similar sticky bit is available for IP unicast frames:
RLEG_UC_IP_OPT_REDIR_STICKY
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if ingress router leg match has been found for an IPv4/IPv6 unicast frame with options/hop-by-hop options. 

Such frames may optionally be redirected to CPU, ref.
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_IP4_OPTIONS_REDIR_ENA
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_IP6_HOPBYHOP_REDIR_ENA

A similar sticky bit is available for IP multicast frames:
RLEG_MC_IP_OPT_REDIR_STICKY
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an ingress router leg match has been found for an IP multicast frame with header errors.

Refer to 
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_RLEG_IP_HDR_FAIL_REDIR_ENA
for list of covered errors.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if an ingress router leg match has been found for an IP unicast frame with header errors.

Refer to 
ANA_L3:COMMON:ROUTING_CFG.CPU_RLEG_IP_HDR_FAIL_REDIR_ENA
for list of covered errors.
------------------------------
<field_public_text>:
Set if ingress router leg match has been found for a non-IP frame. 

Such frames are redirected to 
ANA_L3:COMMON:CPU_QU_CFG.CPU_RLEG_QU
------------------------------
